The paper discusses the challenges of visualizing and mining large multidimensional databases, which are common in fields such as astronomy. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). However, given the focus on indexing techniques and data mining operations, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible given the potential applications of the techniques discussed in the paper.
